<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Jenkins Automation on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ninja-workshops/15-appd-workshop/6-smartagent/2-jenkins-automation/</link><description>Recent content in Jenkins Automation on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ninja-workshops/15-appd-workshop/6-smartagent/2-jenkins-automation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Architecture &amp; Design</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ninja-workshops/15-appd-workshop/6-smartagent/2-jenkins-automation/1-architecture/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/ninja-workshops/15-appd-workshop/6-smartagent/2-jenkins-automation/1-architecture/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="system-architecture"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;System Architecture&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#system-architecture" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Jenkins-based Smart Agent deployment system uses a hub-and-spoke architecture where a Jenkins agent in your AWS VPC orchestrates deployments to multiple target hosts via SSH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="high-level-architecture"&gt;
 &lt;span class="heading-text"&gt;High-Level Architecture&lt;/span&gt;
 &lt;a class="heading-anchor" href="#high-level-architecture" aria-label="Permalink" aria-hidden="true"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/h3&gt;
